Wash and dry all produce. Remove and discard ribs and stems from @kale{4%ounce}. Roughly chop leaves. Halve @grape tomatoes{10%ounce} lengthwise. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @yellow onion{1}.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add @fresh pork chorizo{6%ounce}, breaking it up into pieces, and cook until cooked through and lightly crisped, ~{3-4%minutes}. Remove from pan and set aside. Meanwhile, bring @water{2 1/2%cups} to a boil in a medium #pot{}.

Add onion and a drizzle of oil to same pan over medium-high heat. Cook until soft, ~{4-5%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add tomatoes and cook until just soft, ~{2-3%minutes}. Add @chicken stock concentrate{1}, @water{1/3%cup}, kale, and @smoked paprika{1/2%tsp} (save the rest for garnish). Cook until kale is tender, ~{3-4%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

Once water is boiling, whisk @grits{1/2%cup} into pot. Cook, stirring frequently, until thick, ~{5-7%minutes}. Add a few splashes of water if grits become stiff. Add @cheddar cheese{1/2%cup} and @butter{2%tablespoon} and stir until melted. Season with salt and pepper.

Stir chorizo into pan with veggies.

> TIP: Mixture should have a saucy consistency. Stir in up to 1/4 cup water if it seems dry.

Divide grits between plates. Top with chorizo mixture. Sprinkle with a pinch of smoked paprika and serve.